President Trump welcomed Prime Minister Tsipras of Greece to the White House, emphasizing the long-standing friendship between the two countries and their shared commitment to freedom and sovereignty. They discussed cooperation in defense, energy, commerce, and trade, with President Trump expressing support for Greece's efforts to recover from the economic crisis and implement reform programs. The US also informed Congress of a potential sale to Greece to upgrade its F-16 aircraft, worth up to $2.4 billion. President Trump highlighted Greece's role in European energy security and praised its efforts to attract foreign investment. Prime Minister Tsipras emphasized Greece's economic recovery, its role as a pillar of security cooperation in the region, and its potential as a crossroads for transportation and energy. He mentioned Greece's efforts to tackle bureaucracy and over-taxation to create a friendly environment for foreign investment. Both leaders expressed confidence in Greece's stability and its importance as an ally in the region.